    <string name="about">About</string>
    <string name="about_info_section">Information</string>
    <string name="about_info_data">
    Send shutdown and Wake-on-LAN commands to computers within your local network.\n\n
    Use &#x27F3; gesture on device list to refresh their status in main screen.\n\n
    When using the \"ğŸ” Scan local network\" option the app will try to scan common ports
    to determine if the device is online. Using this feature will also ensure that if the
    \"Remote PC Control Tray\" is running if any of the devices it will return its host name
    and MAC address automatically.
    \n\nPlease keep in mind that due to Android security restrictions sometimes this
    scan doesn\"t return the expected results and some \"online\" machines would not appear.\n\n
    Another source of trouble is the way modern PCs enter hibernation/suspension and how the OS and BIOS
    manage ports in suspension.Some computers will appear as &#x1F534; offline,
    while others will be shown as &#x1F7E2; online or correctly shown as &#x1F7E0; hibernated/suspended.</string>
    <string name="about_options_section">Auto refresh</string>
    <string name="about_options_data">
    Set the \"autorefresh\" option on to scan for computer status changes in the main device list. Set it off
    to use only refresh by &#x27F3; gesture.
